[FMD affects cattle, pigs, and deer but has little effect on human beings.
The rare case of FMD in humans is similar to a mild cold. This disease is
potentially devastating for Britain. They have experienced and endured mad
cow disease, or BSE (Bovine Spongiform Encephalopathy) as well as a recent
outbreak of Classical Swine Fever (CSF) ­ Mod.TG
